            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51674",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can you please test against current master? I believe a PR was merged earlier this week fixing this issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-22T20:23:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-22T20:23:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51676",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=taisph",
                        "name": "taisph",
                        "displayName": "Tais Plougmann Hansen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Master fails with following error:\r\n\r\nUnable to connect to ssl:\/\/accounts.google.com:443. Error #0: stream_socket_client(): unable to connect to ssl:\/\/accounts.google.com:443 (Unknown error)\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=taisph",
                        "name": "taisph",
                        "displayName": "Tais Plougmann Hansen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-22T21:07:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-22T21:07:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51678",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "A few notes:\r\n\r\n1. The \"error #0\" thing comes from OpenSSL \/ PHP's openssl extension. There's no way to get a better message, at least not after digging into this for quite some time. There's also no way to assume the error is specifically a peer verification error. In short, PHP itself or maybe OpenSSL hides it from us, and there's little we can do about it. \r\n\r\n2. The path varies, but on quite a lot of installations it \"just works\" as the OpenSSL lib linked to PHP knows where to look for certs - at least that's what I've seen several times. \r\n\r\nMy recommendation would be to put a big note in the docs but not change the behavior from what it is now. Unless someone can find a way to get a better error code \/ message from OpenSSL. \r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-22T21:34:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-22T21:34:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51680",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=taisph",
                        "name": "taisph",
                        "displayName": "Tais Plougmann Hansen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This happens on a stock Ubuntu 12.04.1 LTS with latest Zend Server 5.6.0. It would be nice to know whether this is then caused by Zend Server or Ubuntu, since I'm pretty confident this will bite a lot of people given the platform's popularity.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=taisph",
                        "name": "taisph",
                        "displayName": "Tais Plougmann Hansen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-23T07:47:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-23T07:47:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51681",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It's likely that it's a Zend Server related issue, because it ships with it's own OpenSSL but without any SSL certificates, and doesn't know to locate them at \/etc\/ssl\/certs (as it builds generically for different Linux distros). \r\n\r\nI have seen it work on different setups, but I do not know if it works on most of them or not. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-23T07:53:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-23T07:53:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51682",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=taisph",
                        "name": "taisph",
                        "displayName": "Tais Plougmann Hansen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Actually, it seems like ZS uses the system SSL. libphp5.so (and .\/configure in php -i output) both seem to link to the system openssl libs. So this is looking more like an Ubuntu issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=taisph",
                        "name": "taisph",
                        "displayName": "Tais Plougmann Hansen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-23T08:00:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-23T08:00:15.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/52024",
                    "author": {
